e beautiful can be related to the morally good. On the basis of this reinterpreted concept of form, most major concepts and themes of the Critique of Judgment—such as disinterestedness, free play, the sublime, genius, and beautiful arts—are examined by the author and shown in a new light.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aAesthetics, Moderny18th century. 4aPhilosophy -- Aesthetics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478031540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804780315423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804780315/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles